    <bioghist id="aspace_hzc215657n545as12442499742879">
      <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
      <p>Established in 1947 as a commercial art gallery by librarians at the Santa Monica Library, the gallery exhibited abstract art from 1947 to 1965 when the building was torn down. The gallery exhibited mostly local and amatuer artists, with exceptions like Hans Burkhardt, Wayne Thiebaud, Helen Lundeberg, Stanton Macdanold-Wright, June Wayne, Rico Lebrun, Lorser Feitelson, Francis de Erdely, and Bill Brice.</p>
    </bioghist>
    <arrangement id="aspace_5fca847e4b4443faa3df95e83ab843b9">
      <head>Arrangement</head>
      <p>The collection is arranged as one series.</p>
      <list type="ordered">
        <item>Series 1: Santa Monica Art Gallery, 1953-1967(0.4 linear feet; Box 1)</item>
      </list>
    </arrangement>
    <scopecontent id="aspace_hzc215657n520as44441562078905">
      <head>Scope and Contents</head>
      <p>The small selection of records of the Santa Monica Art Gallery measure 0.4 linear feet and date from 1953 to 1967. The records document the history of the gallery through artist statements, correspondence with Round the World Tours, and photographs.</p>
    </scopecontent>
